				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I do think it is significantly easier to port amongst the same CPU. Much better than if they had a different CPU. Doesn't mean it's easy. Just easier. There are tons and tons of games that got ported between Amiga and Atari ST, for example. Even more recently, portability between XBox360 and PS3 was made a ton easier because they both had PowerPC architecture.<br /><br />Now, if you want to find examples where code was shared, go looking. Maybe check out Paperboy on the NES and C64 and see if you can find the same routines in each? Might be tricky to compare, since relocation of code is going to change most of the addresses, but maybe an instruction comparison on trace logs might help find similar regions of code, if they exist. Probably it'd be a lot of work to answer this question properly; would anyone care enough to find out?</div>

